			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I seem to remember reading that the only modification from the original 6502 to the 2A03's CPU core was erasing the part of the chip that had the decimal mode circuitry, as Ricoh couldn't afford to license that from MOS Technology. That wouldn't have changed the values of the don't cares in the decoder gate array, which is where most of the extra instructions come from. But anything that involves $EE or $EF or $11 or other values where bit 4 is prominent might have changed behavior, as those values seem to originate from decimal mode.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

